{"lemma":"جُبَّةٌ","slug":"جُبَّةٌ","root":"ج.ب.ب","root_slug":"ج-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4906"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hit or strike someone's forehead","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ج ب ه (j b h). Compare جَبْهَة (jabha, “forehead”)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.ba.ha/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4906","headword_ar":"جُبَّةٌ","root":"jb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coat"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the kind of those called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqaT~aEaAt","text_ar":"مُقَطَّعَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) accord. to ' Iyád,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment cut out and sewed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to Ibn-Hajar and others,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a double garment quilted with cotton;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, sometimes, if"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wool, a single garment, not quilted with anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MF:) [most probably not so much resembling the modern garment more generally known by the same name (for a description and representation of which see my “ Modern Egyptians, ” ch. i.,) as a kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"still worn in Northern Africa, described in this Lexicon voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"midoraEapN","text_ar":"مِدْرَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to Golius,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"“ tunica ex panno gossipino,"},{"kind":"text","text":"cui pallium seu toga imponitur,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cum subductitio panno et intercedente gossipio punctim consuta:"},{"kind":"text","text":"Italis consona voce"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"giuppa:"},{"kind":"text","text":"si ita cum gossipio consuta non sit,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aAEapN","text_ar":"دُرَّاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"tunica illa gossipina dicitur: ”] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jubabN","text_ar":"جُبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jibaAbN","text_ar":"جِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroEN","text_ar":"دِرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A coat of mail;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any coat of defence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jubabN","text_ar":"جُبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Er-Rá'ee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lanaA jubabN waA^aromaAHN TiwaAlN\n                      \n                     \n                        bihin~a numaArisu AlHaroba Al$~aTuwnaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have coats of mail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of defence, and long spears: with them we ply distant war"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a spear-head"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into which the shaft enters:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaEolab","text_ar":"ثَعْلَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the part of the spear-shaft that enters into the head. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [In the TA,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~apu Alr~umoHi","text_ar":"جُبَّةُ الرُّمْحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also explained as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA dxl mn AlsnAn fyh","text_ar":"ما دخل من السنان فيه"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part of the spearhead that enters into the shaft:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but it seems that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"text","text":"has been inserted here by a mistake of the copyist; and that the true meaning intended is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the part of the spear-shaft into which the head enters;"},{"kind":"text","text":"though in general the shaft enters into the head.] ―         -b3-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part in which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aA$ap","text_ar":"مُشَاشَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.] of a horn. (Zeyd Ibn-Kuthweh, TA.) ―         -b4-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HijaAj","text_ar":"حِجَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone that surrounds the cavity"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hj","text_ar":"حج"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the eye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contents"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ha$ow","text_ar":"حَشْو"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the solid hoof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"horny box"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaron","text_ar":"قَرْن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the solid hoof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAq","text_ar":"ساق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which seems to mean here, as it does in many other instances, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hind shank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the thigh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shank-joint"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse or the like ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoSilu AlwaZiyfi","text_ar":"مَوْصِلُ الوَظِيفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[commonly applied, as in the S and K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rusog","text_ar":"رُسْغ"},{"kind":"text","text":", to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper extremity of the pastern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fetlock-joint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which seems to be the meaning intended in this instance,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAE","text_ar":"ذِرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which here app. means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fore leg,"},{"kind":"text","text":"not the arm]: or, accord. to As, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wZyf","text_ar":"وظيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shank"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is set into the hoof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rsg","text_ar":"رسغ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pastern"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a horse, where the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wZyf","text_ar":"وظيف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shank"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joins upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawo$ab","text_ar":"حَوْشَب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which seems here to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper pasternbone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or, as AO says, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part where a horse's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wZyf","text_ar":"وظيف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joins to the upper part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw$b","text_ar":"حوشب"},{"kind":"text","text":": or, as he says in another place, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place where each tibia and hind shank, of a horse, meet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hockjoint;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mltqY sAqyh wwZyfY rjlyh","text_ar":"ملتقى ساقيه ووظيفى رجليه"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of junction of any two bones, except in the back-bone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Accord. to Lth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whiteness of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bTAnyp","text_ar":"بطانية"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a word which I have not found anywhere but in this instance]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a horse or similar beast, extending to the hairs that surround the hoof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","TA","MF","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}